## EXAMPLE FINDING

```yaml
finding:
  id: ARCH-001
  category: Architecture
  subcategory: Types
  severity: HIGH
  file: src/pages/general-foreman/GeneralForemanEquipmentLogs.tsx
  line: 45
  observed_condition: |
    API response is cast to `any` then accessed without type guards.
    This bypasses TypeScript's safety and can cause runtime errors.
  evidence: |
    const { data } = useQuery('equipment-logs', fetchLogs);
    const logs = data as any; // Type assertion to any
    return logs.map((log) => log.someField); // No type safety
  impact: |
    If API shape changes, no compile-time error. Runtime crash likely.
    Maintenance burden: developers must trace API to know shape.
  recommendation: |
    1. Define EquipmentLog interface
    2. Type the useQuery generic
    3. Remove `any` cast
  dod: |
    1. No `any` types in file
    2. npx tsc --noEmit passes
    3. API response typed with interface
  effort: S
  dependencies: none
```

